The paper deals with error-correcting codes in optical communications, which suggests that it falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) categories. The paper also discusses a low-complexity method for resolving stall patterns, which could potentially involve data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper introduces an improved error floor analysis, which could be related to the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) category.
